  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6525.08 sitting right at max positive gamma but in BREAKOUT regime, dealers are caught in a whipsaw position - they're selling rallies here while simultaneously being short overall gamma, creating conflicting hedging pressures that explain the extreme 1-min/-99.2% vs 5-min/+82.6% volatility swings. The wall break and GEX surge events suggest dealers just got steamrolled and are now scrambling to re-hedge, with the 6533 flip strike only 8 points away acting as the critical pivot - above it, dealer selling accelerates into the 6550 negative wall, while any dip toward 6520 support should see modest stabilization before the massive 6515 buy wall kicks in. Watch for explosive moves if we breach either 6533 to the upside (trend continuation) or 6515 to the downside (capitulation), as the negative gamma regime will amplify any directional momentum.",
